This drink marries scrumptious cognac, Canadian maple syrup, lemon juice, orange bitters and bone-dry cider to create a complex yet approachable tipple that’s hard to have just the one of. Serves 1 50ml good cognac – we use Rémy Martin 173810ml maple syrup 10ml fresh lemon juice 1 dash orange bittersDry French cider, to topOrange zest, to garnish Fill a shaker with ice, add all the liquids bar the cider, shake and strain into a highball glass filled with fresh ice. Top with the cider, garnish and serve. • Designed by Happiness Forgets bar, London N1, for Maison Rémy Martin at Claude Bosi, Bibendum, London SW3